class Person:
    """
    This class defines a Person
    """
    ###here __init__ is used as a constuctor
    ###self is always used in program
    def __init__(self, name, age, gender, occupation):
        
        self.name = name
        self.age = age
        self.gender = gender
        self.occupation = occupation
        
    def introduce(self):
        """
        This class introduce a person
        """
        print(f'Hi there myself {self.name}')
        print(f'I am {self.age} years old')
        print(f'I am a {self.gender}')
        print(f'I work as a {self.occupation}')
    
    def work(self, company):
        """
        This function talks about work of person
        """
        print(f'{self.name} works in {company}')

class Account:
    
    def __init__(self, ac_no, name , balance):
        self.ac_no = ac_no
        self.name = name
        self.balance = balance
    
    def deposit(self, amt):
        self.balance = self.balance + amt
        print(f'Money of {amt} INR is credited into : {self.ac_no} ')
        print(f'Current Balance is : {self.balance} INR')
    
    def withdraw(self, amt):
        if self.balance >=  amt:
            self.balance = self.balance - amt
            print(f'Money of {amt} INR is debited from your account : {self.ac_no} ')
            print(f'Current Balance is : {self.balance} INR')
        else:
            print(f'Insufficient balance in your : {self.ac_no}')
            print(f'Current Balance is : {self.balance} INR')
            
    def transfer(self, tr_ac , amt):
        if self.balance >= amt:
            self.balance = self.balance - amt
            tr_ac.balance = tr_ac.balance + amt
            print(f'Money of {amt} INR is debited from your account  : {self.ac_no} to {tr_ac.ac_no}')
            print(f'Current Balance is : {self.balance} INR')
        else:
            print(f'Insufficient balance in your : {self.ac_no}')
            print(f'Current Balance is : {self.balance} INR')

1:- Formation of triangle : Sum of 2 sides should be greater than 3rd

2:- Perimeter : Sum of all sides of triangle (a+b+c)

3:- Area of triangle : A=sqrt(s(sa)*(sb(sc))

4:- s=(a+b+c)/2

In [66]:
class Triangle:
    
    def __init__(self,a , b, c):
        self.a = a
        self.b = b
        self.c = c
        
    def isTriangle(self):
        a = self.a
        b = self.b
        c = self.c
        if (a+b>c) and (a+c>b) and (b+c>a):
            tr = True
        else:
            tr = False
        return tr
    
    def perimeter(self):
        if self.isTriangle() == True:
            p = self.a + self.b +self.c
        else:
            p= None
            print(f'Sides {self.a} , {self.b} , {self.c} do NOT form a Triangle')
        return p
    

            
    def area(self):
        if self.isTriangle()==True:
            s = self.perimeter()/2
            a = (s*(s-self.a)*(s-self.b)*(s-self.c))**(1/2)
        else:
            a = None
            print(f'The sides {self.a}, {self.b} and {self.c} DO NOT FORM a Triangle')
        return a

Triangle example with decorator¶

Decorator - Outside

In [123]:
 def triangleCheck(func):
        def wrapper(self, *args, **kwargs):
            if self.isTriangle()==True:
                f = func(self, *args, **kwargs)
            else:
                f = None
                print(f'The sides {self.a}, {self.b} and {self.c} DO NOT FORM a Triangle')
            return f
        return wrapper
In [124]:
@triangleCheck
class Triangle:
    
    def __init__(self, a, b, c):
        self.a = a
        self.b = b
        self.c = c
        
    def isTriangle(self):
        a = self.a
        b = self.b
        c = self.c
        if (a+b>c) and (b+c>a) and (c+a)>b:
            tr = True
        else:
            tr = False
        return tr   
    
    @triangleCheck
    def perimeter(self):
        p = self.a + self.b + self.c
        return p
    
    @triangleCheck
    def area(self):
        s = self.perimeter()/2
        a = (s*(s-self.a)*(s-self.b)*(s-self.c))**(1/2)
        return a

        div = num / den
        return div
    except ZeroDivisionError:

Try Except Finally block¶

1:- Code will execute try block

2:- if any error/exception occurs it will go to except block

3:- finally block will always execute

In [ ]:
def calculate_sqr_root():
    try:
        n = float(input("Enter a number : "))
        import math
        s = math.sqrt(n)
        return s
    except Exception as e:
        print (f'Exception occured :{e}')
    finally:
        print("Fianlly block is always executed")
